					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<extent>50 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>217</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>162</height>
										<width>100</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>50 folios (+ 4 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of 6 to 8 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Water-damaged, especially upper and lower margins.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="39" writtenLines="39">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Pricking and pencil ruling is visible.</p>
									<p>Initial words in each section is given in larger characters, and in red ink on folios 1r-10v.</p>
									<p>Last line written outside ruling.</p>
									<p>Some marginal notes and additions are present.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi semi-cursive script of the 15th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>The parchment flyleaf at the beginning and at the end: parts of Spanish calendar of the 14th to 15th century: [iv recto], [iv verso], [51r], [51v].</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Dominico Irosolomitano</name>, Italian censor (active in the last quarter of the 16th and first quarter of the 17th century): inscribed with his name (folio 50v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">61</ref>, and appendix § 62-74.
</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Giovanni Domenico Carretto</name>, Italian censor (active in the first quarter of the 17th century): inscribed with his name, 1628? (folio 50r); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">100-101</ref>, and appendix § 80-84. </p>
						</additions>
